	<p style="htitle">Substations</p>
	<p style="hp">Substations take power packets from power lines (high-voltage) and distribute the power to adjacent transport (low-voltage). Check the power overlay to see where you need more power. The transformers don't require any labor to function.</p>

  <p style="hp">This is a substation</p>
   <img src="images/tiles/substation-G.png" halign="center"/>

  <p style="hp">and this is its icon</p>
   <img src="images/gui/buttonpanel/power/substation.png" halign="center"/>

	<p style="hsubtitle">Formulas</p>
	<p style="hp">1500 hi-volt =&gt; 3000 lo-volt</p>
	<p style="hp">If there is not enough high-voltage power, then the formula may be scaled down.</p>

